\f5\fs30 \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 AT&T is rethinking \'93Rethink possible.\'94\cb1 \
\cb3 AT&T adopted \'93Rethink possible\'94 as the theme of its advertising in a\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/08/business/media/08adco.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf9 \ul \ulc9 \strokec9 corporate image campaign}}\'a0that began in April 2010. The upbeat theme was intended to buff the AT&T brand, rather than sell specific products and services, and promote the company as an innovator in telecommunications for consumer and business customers.\cb1 \
\cb3 Two years later, the campaign is being refreshed with ads that are to begin appearing on Monday, some of which will help introduce the\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/03/29/att-lumia-900"}}{\fldrslt \cf9 \ul \ulc9 \strokec9 Nokia Lumia 900}}\'a0smartphone. The campaign includes commercials on television and online and a robust presence in social media like\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.facebook.com/ATT"}}{\fldrslt \cf9 \ul \ulc9 \strokec9 Facebook}},\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://twitter.com/#!/ATT"}}{\fldrslt \cf9 \ul \ulc9 \strokec9 Twitter}}\'a0and blogs.\cb1 \
\cb3 The new elements of the campaign will include the addition, in ads aimed at consumers, of the phrase \'93It\'92s what you do with what we do.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl450\partightenfactor0
\cf8 \cb3 The phrase, which will appear along with \'93Rethink possible,\'94 is meant to acknowledge significant shifts in the marketplace since 2010, particularly how much more consumers want to be in control of brand experiences.\cb1 \
