\f5\fs30 \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 \'93We did a lot of insight research about how people live with technology,\'94 said Esther Lee, senior vice president for brand marketing, advertising and sponsorship at AT&T in Dallas, which included \'93ethnographies, shop-alongs and spending time in people\'92s living rooms.\'94\cb1 \
\cb3 When the \'93Rethink possible\'94 campaign was developed, most consumers \'93felt overwhelmed with technology,\'94 Ms. Lee said, but only a short time later many have \'93found ways to integrate it in their lives\'94 \'97 and some even \'93talk about it with love.\'94\cb1 \
\cb3 \'93The real innovation that\'92s happening is what people are doing, and how people are dealing, with technology,\'94 she added, and \'93the unique ways they use it to make their lives better.\'94\cb1 \
