\fs30 \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 Unlike the fast-food themes, which were focused on the \'93we\'94 \'97 that is, the advertiser \'97 the AT&T ads are \'93all about you, the consumer, and how we\'92re proud to help you do what you can do,\'94 said David Lubars, chairman and chief creative officer at BBDO North America, part of the BBDO Worldwide unit of the Omnicom Group. The Atlanta and New York offices of BBDO North America serve as the creative agency for AT&T.\cb1 \
\cb3 \'93It\'92s the difference between \'91We prepared a meal for you\'92 and \'91We\'92re your partner,\'92\'a0\'94 Mr. Lubars said.\cb1 \
\cb3 There was no thought given to replacing \'93Rethink possible\'94 because \'93it\'92s still an idea that resonates with people,\'94 he added. \'93You don\'92t want to change it because it\'92s relevant.\'94\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl450\partightenfactor0
\cf8 \cb3 By augmenting the theme with the new phrase, Mr. Lubars said, \'93we put a new suit on\'94 the campaign and emphasized \'93how people\'92s lives are entwined with technology\'94 and the benefits of \'93life on the network\'94 (the AT&T network, natch).\cb1 \
